%global packname  fastrtext
%global packver   0.3.3
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          0.3.3
Release:          1%{?dist}
Summary:          'fastText' Wrapper for Text Classification and WordRepresentation

License:          MIT + file LICENSE
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel >= 3.3
Requires:         R-core >= 3.3
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-Rcpp >= 0.12.12
BuildRequires:    R-methods 
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-assertthat 
Requires:         R-CRAN-Rcpp >= 0.12.12
Requires:         R-methods 
Requires:         R-CRAN-assertthat 

%description
Learning text representations and text classifiers may rely on the same
simple and efficient approach. 'fastText' is an open-source, free,
lightweight library that allows users to perform both tasks. It transforms
text into continuous vectors that can later be used on many language
related task. It works on standard, generic hardware (no 'GPU' required).
It also includes model size reduction feature. 'fastText' original source
code is available at <https://github.com/facebookresearch/fastText>.

